"Broad ligament of uterus","Ligament of ovary","Round ligament of uterus","Suspensory ligament of ovary","Transverse cervical ligament"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esuspensory ligament of ovary\u003C/strong\u003E (also known as the infundibulopelvic ligament) extends from the lateral pelvic wall to the ovary and contains the ovarian vessels and nerves. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ebroad ligament of uterus\u003C/strong\u003E is a double fold of peritoneum that extends from the sides of the uterus to the lateral pelvic walls. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eround ligament of uterus\u003C/strong\u003E extends from the uterus through the inguinal canal to the labia majora. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eligament of ovary\u003C/strong\u003E connects the ovary to the lateral aspect of the uterus. The \u003Cstrong\u003Etransverse cervical ligament\u003C/strong\u003E (cardinal ligament) extends from the cervix and upper vagina to the lateral pelvic walls.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The suspensory ligament of the ovary contains the ovarian vessels and nerves and it extends from the lateral pelvic wall to the ovary","The suspensory ligament of the ovary is also known as the infundibulopelvic ligament"],"references":["Cheng LK, O\u0027Grady G, Du P, Egbuji JU, Windsor JA, Pullan AJ. Gastrointestinal system. Wiley Interdiscip Rev Syst Biol Med. 2010 Jan-Feb;2(1):65-79. doi: 10.1002/wsbm.19. PMID: 20836011; PMCID: PMC4221587","Kahai P, Mandiga P, Wehrle CJ, Lobo S. Anatomy, Abdomen and Pelvis: Large Intestine. In: StatPearls. StatPearls Publishing, Treasure Island (FL); 2023. PMID: 29261962","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51381"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15666"}},"stemMedia":